to Hellenistic poetry. This is now demonstrated for all 48 of Catullus’ epigrams using methods of modern literary scholarship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCatull. 0aEpigramm. 0aHellenistische Dichtung. 0aIntertextualität. 0aLyrik. 4aCatull. 4aEpigramm. 4aHellenistische Dichtung. 4aIntertextualität. 4aLyrik. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aCatullus.  aEpigram.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2007z9783110277005oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311019466140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089891040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110898910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110898910/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014